CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, January 17, 1938, pg. unknown, reads: "'Charming Matrons and Petite Maids all, the ever-ready camera-man presents this photo of the membership of the most exclusive of all the social clubs in Pgh., the Matron's and Maid's. (Photos by Cameraman Chas. 'Teenie' Harris)."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of women, including Harriet Lewis second from left in front, Jessie Vann wearing sequinned jacket in second row, and Charlotte Enty Catlin wearing braids around ears on right, gathered in Loendi Club with Christmas tree in background
